            <title>[CASSANDRA-6695] Don&apos;t exchange schema between nodes with different versions (no pull, no push)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-6695</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Subject. Don&apos;t push schema to unknown-, or differently major-versioned nodes, and don&apos;t pull schema from them, either.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since we don&apos;t support schema altering during upgrade, and adding nodes during cluster upgrades is also a non-recommended thing, this is what we are going to do.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Until &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-6038&quot; title=&quot;Support schema changes in mixed version clusters&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-6038&quot;&gt;CASSANDRA-6038&lt;/a&gt;, that is.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
